        Open Positions
    






Look at Meridian:


If you're looking for a job where
                        innovative and creative thinking, accountability, and results-driven leadership
                        can lead to exciting new career growth opportunities, look no further than Meridian
                        Bioscience. Our diverse and
                            talented associates are committed to our mission of bringing innovative new products
                            and technologies to market that improve the diagnosis and treatment of infectious
                            diseases and metabolic disorders.


"In a word, this
                        place is all about opportunity."
                            — Reddy Ponaka, Senior Scientist


                     

Click
                        the link below to access our online application process.

Apply For A Position At Meridian




                    Accessibility


If you're a qualified individual
                        with a disability or a disabled veteran, and you require reasonable accommodation
                        for any part of the application or hiring process, you may submit your request by
                        sending an email to HR@meridianbioscience.com,
                        or by faxing it to 513-272-5433. Please note this option is reserved for individuals
                        who require accommodation because of a disability. Information received will be
                        routed to a recruiter who will provide assistance to ensure appropriate consideration
                        in the application or hiring process.



                        Equal Employment Opportunity

Meridian Bioscience, Inc. (MBI) is
                        an equal opportunity employer. MBI offers employment and advancement opportunities
                        based on performance and qualifications, regardless of race, color, national origin, sex, age, religion, sexual orientation, gender identity, disability or veteran status. To provide equal
                        employment and advancement opportunities to all individuals, employment decisions
                        at MBI are based on merit, qualifications, and abilities. This policy governs all
                        aspects of employment, including selection, job assignment, promotion, compensation,
                        discipline, termination, and access to benefits and training.


MBI maintains an affirmative action
                        program to implement our EEO policy. Employees or applicants who wish to review
                        appropriate portions of this program to see how it benefits them may do so by making
                        an appointment with Human Resources.


                    Click here for EEO is the Law Poster



                        Meridian Departments



Corporate Finance 



Regulatory Affairs/Quality Assurance 



Research and Development (R&D) 



Sales and Marketing 



Finished Goods Production 



Para Pak Production 



Laboratory Production 



Materials Management 



MIS Information Services and Technology




Operations Control and Support (OCS)




Purification 









Corporate Finance is responsible for Meridian's treasury and external
                        financial reporting functions. These include accounting, cash management, debt/equity
                        capital apportioning, and external reporting of financial results to shareholders,
                        the Securities and Exchange Commission and other interested parties. Meridian's
                        Finance Group is also involved in modeling and evaluating return potential for various
                        business investments (e.g., acquisitions, alliances, new products and other transactions).
                        

Regulatory Affairs/Quality
                            Assurance ensures that Meridian complies with all applicable company,
                        state and federal policies and regulations relating to the quality of its products
                        and services. This group facilitates 3rd party audits (including FDA and ISO audits),
                        prepares product registrations for new products or product modifications, and maintains
                        annual registrations with the EPA, ATF, DEA, and USDA.
                        

Research and Development (R&D)
                        leads the company in the development of innovative products to enhance the corporate
                        market position in the biotech industry. The R&D team also strives continually
                        to improve existing products to ensure customer needs are met.
                        

Sales and Marketing is responsible
                        for customer sales in the U.S., Canada, South America, Europe and the Pacific Rim.
                        Its function is to market and sell Meridian's products to customers via direct sales
                        and distribution partners.
                        

Finished Goods Production 
                        manufactures and assembles dependable diagnostic test kits in their proper format
                        for shipment to our customers. This would include all diagnostic products manufactured
                        by Meridian.
                        

Para Pak Production furnishes our
                        customers with a unique product for safely transporting fecal specimens. The agents
                        are formulated, filled, and packaged in this department.
                        

Laboratory Production consists
                        of trained technicians who produce the bulk antigens, antibodies and reagents that
                        are then given to Finished Goods Production for the final part of the manufacturing
                        process. Processes used by Laboratory Production involve formulation, bacterial/fungal
                        growth, tissue culture, protein assay and spectrophotometry.
                        

Materials Management coordinates
                        the planning, ordering and purchasing of raw materials used in the manufacturing
                        of current products and all other materials as needed. In addition, the department
                        develops cost reduction programs in an effort to reduce overall costs to the company.
                        

MIS Information Services and
                            Technology is a support organization. Both internal and external customers
                        benefit from the support of various hardware/software systems.
                        

Operations Control and Support (OCS)
                        consists of scientists and engineers who support manufacturing and R&D. OCS
                        employees perform Investigations, Validations, and Process Improvements. Investigations
                        and Validations develop, write and execute protocols, which enable Manufacturing
                        and R&D to not only problem-solve but also transfer new technology into Manufacturing.
                        Both groups propose and implement process improvements that improve product quality
                        and processing efficiency while reducing the cost of manufacturing.
                        

Purification ensures purity of antibodies
                        and antigens used in Meridian's diagnostic products. The type of purification and
                        the quality of our antibodies and antigens separate our products from those of our
                        competitors. 










Learn more about Meridian 











See how Meridian is helping to make a
                            difference














