Meridian Bioscience Inc. (NASDAQ:VIVO) Experiences Lighter than Usual Trading Volume 












































 Finance DailyDaily markets, commodities, personal finance and economic newsMeridian Bioscience Inc. (NASDAQ:VIVO) Experiences Lighter than Usual Trading Volume
July 26, 2017 By Ted Blackburn Tweet
        Advertisement



Trading volume for Meridian Bioscience Inc. was 4,147 on Wednesday.  Trading volume was down 98.71% under the stocks average daily volume. 
 Traders are a little more bullish on shares of Meridian Bioscience Inc. of late as implied by the motion in short interest.  The company recorded a fall in short interest between June 15, 2017 and May 31, 2017 of -0.57%.  Short shares decreased 21,371 over that timeframe.  The short-interest ratio decreased to 11.0 and the percentage of shorted shares was 0.09% on May 31. 
 These firms have also modified their investment in VIVO.   Russell Investments Group, Ltd. trimmed its ownership by shedding 26,867 shares a decrease of 87.5% from 03/31/2017 to 06/30/2017. Russell Investments Group, Ltd. owns 3,851 shares worth $61,000. The value of the position overall is down by 85.6%. As of quarter end Greylin Investment Mangement Inc had bought 10,050 shares growing its holdings by 19.7%. The value of the investment in Meridian Bioscience Inc. increased from $706,000 to $964,000 a change of $258,000 quarter over quarter.
 Btim Corp. divested its stake by selling 38,600 shares a decrease of 15.1%. Btim Corp. currently owns 217,200 shares with a value of $3,421,000. The total value of its holdings decreased 3.1%. As of the end of the quarter Aperio Group, LLC had acquired  a total of 14,682 shares growing its position 40.0%. The value of the investment in VIVO went from $507,000 to $809,000 a change of 59.6% since the last quarter.
  On July 29 the company was rated “Hold” in a report from Hilliard Lyons which is down from the previous “Buy” rating. On March 28 the company was upgraded to “Buy” from “Neutral” with a current price target of $22.00 by analysts at Hilliard Lyons.        Advertisement






 On March 21, 2016 the stock rating was changed to a “Neutral” by Hilliard Lyons which was a cut from the previous “Long-term Buy” rating. On September 10 Canaccord Genuity left the company rating at “Hold” but lowered the price target  to $18.00 from $19.00.
 July 27 investment analysts at Canaccord Genuity made no change to the company rating of “Hold” and lowered the price target from $20.00 to $19.00. May 4 investment analysts at Canaccord Genuity maintained a stock rating of “Hold” but moved up the price target from $19.00 to $20.00.
 The company is trading unchanged by 0.00 percent from yesterday’s close.  Meridian Bioscience Inc. also declared a dividend for shareholders paid on Thursday May 18th, 2017.  The dividend was $0.125 per share for the quarter which is $0.50 annualized.  This dividend represents a yeild of $3.30 which is the dividend as a percentage of the current share price.  The ex-dividend date was set for Thursday the 4th of May 2017. 
 The stock last traded at $15.25 marginally under $15.27, the 50 day moving average and just a bit higher than the 200 day moving average of $14.24.  The 50 day moving average went down by -0.11% and the 200 day average moved up $1.01. 
 The most current P/E ratio is 21.51 and the market value is 643.58M.  As of the latest earnings report the EPS was $0.71 and is estimated to be $0.68 for the current year with 42,202,000 shares currently outstanding.  Next quarter’s EPS is forecasted at $0.15 and the next full year EPS is anticipated to be $0.70. 
 Meridian Bioscience, Inc., launched on June 25, 1976, is a life science company. The Company is involved in the development, manufacture, sale and distribution of diagnostic test kits for gastrointestinal, viral, respiratory and parasitic infectious diseases, and elevated blood lead levels, and the manufacture and distribution of bulk antigens, antibodies, polymerase chain reaction (PCR)/quantitative PCR (qPCR) reagents, nucleotides, competent cells and bioresearch reagents used by researchers and other diagnostic manufacturers. The Business’s segments include Diagnostics and Life Science. The Diagnostics segment consists of manufacturing operations in Cincinnati, Ohio, and the sale and distribution of diagnostic test kits in the countries consisting of North, Central and South America (the Americas); Europe, Middle East and Africa (EMEA), and other countries outside of the Americas and EMEA (rest of the world (ROW)). Its facility includes research, development, manufacturing, marketing, sales and distribution operations. The Life Science segment consists of manufacturing operations in Memphis, Tennessee; Boca Raton, Florida; London, England; Luckenwalde, Germany, and Sydney, Australia..
